data: {"type":"result","content":" Clinical Utility of MRD in Prognostication\n\nThe achievement of complete morphologic remission (CR) "}

data: {"type":"result","content":"has long served as a primary endpoint in AML therapy and a prerequisite for long-term survival. Howe"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"ver, conventional CR assessment lacks sensitivity to detect low-level disease that often drives subs"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"equent relapse. MRD assessment provides a more sensitive measure of treatment response that has demo"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"nstrated significant prognostic value across multiple clinical trials and patient populations.\n\nThe "}

data: {"type":"result","content":"prognostic significance of MRD status post-induction therapy has been consistently demonstrated in p"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"rospective studies. The UK National Cancer Research Institute (NCRI) AML trials established that MRD"}

data: {"type":"result","content":" positivity following induction chemotherapy identified patients at substantially higher risk for re"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"lapse, regardless of their baseline cytogenetic risk category. In their landmark analysis of over 2,"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"000 patients, MRD-positive patients experienced approximately three-fold higher relapse rates compar"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"ed to MRD-negative counterparts, with corresponding reductions in overall survival.\n\nThe HOVON/SAKK "}

data: {"type":"result","content":"collaborative group further validated these findings, demonstrating that flow cytometry-based MRD as"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"sessment after cycle 2 of induction therapy strongly predicted relapse-free survival (RFS) and overa"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"ll survival (OS). Their analysis revealed that MRD positivity was associated with a 4-year RFS of on"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"ly 32% compared to 76% in MRD-negative patients. This predictive power remained significant in multi"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"variate analysis incorporating standard risk factors including cytogenetics and molecular mutations."}

data: {"type":"result","content":"\n\nThe prognostic value of MRD extends beyond the post-induction setting. The ALFA group demonstrated"}

data: {"type":"result","content":" that MRD assessment following consolidation therapy provided additional discriminatory power for re"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"lapse prediction. In their analysis, patients who achieved MRD negativity after consolidation showed"}

data: {"type":"result","content":" significantly improved leukemia-free survival compared to those with persistent MRD, even among pat"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"ients who had been MRD-positive following induction. This finding highlights the dynamic nature of M"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"RD assessment and its utility throughout the treatment course.\n\nMolecular MRD monitoring has shown p"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"articular value in specific genetic subgroups. For patients with NPM1 mutations, quantitative PCR-ba"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"sed MRD monitoring enables highly sensitive disease tracking. Studies have demonstrated that NPM1 mu"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"tation clearance after chemotherapy identifies patients with favorable outcomes, while persistence o"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"r reemergence of mutated NPM1 transcripts strongly predicts imminent clinical relapse. Similarly, in"}

data: {"type":"result","content":" core-binding factor AML (characterized by RUNX1-RUNX1T1 or CBFB-MYH11 fusions), molecular MRD monit"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"oring provides powerful prognostic information that can guide post-remission therapy decisions.\n\nMRD"}

data: {"type":"result","content":" assessment also refines prognostication within established risk groups. Among patients with adverse"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"-risk cytogenetics, achievement of MRD negativity identifies a subset with relatively favorable outc"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"omes who may not require immediate transplantation in first remission. Conversely, detection of MRD "}

data: {"type":"result","content":"in otherwise favorable-risk patients flags those who may benefit from treatment intensification desp"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"ite their seemingly good-risk profile.\n\nThe kinetics of MRD clearance provides additional prognostic"}

data: {"type":"result","content":" information beyond single time-point assessment. Rapid achievement of MRD negativity after initial "}

data: {"type":"result","content":"induction cycles correlates with superior long-term outcomes, while persistent MRD despite multiple "}

data: {"type":"result","content":"therapy cycles indicates chemoresistant disease with poor prognosis. Serial MRD monitoring during fo"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"llow-up enables early identification of molecular relapse, potentially allowing for preemptive inter"}

data: {"type":"result","content":"vention before overt clinical recurrence.\n\nDespite these consistent findings, several challenges rem"}

